{"product_id":"the-orange-the-california-dream","title":"The Orange \u0026 The California Dream","description":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eThe Orange and the Dream of California\u003c\/em\u003e takes a lively, literary, and extraordinarily visual look at the symbiotic relationship between the Golden State and its \"golden apple,\" a pairing that resulted in a compelling fantasy and a fantastic reality. \u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUntold numbers of people came West in the twentieth century lured by postcards showing orange blossoms juxtaposed with snow-capped mountains. And across the country, daily glasses of navel orange juice were a must after Sunkist's \u003cem\u003eMad Men\u003c\/em\u003e-style campaign spread the word that drinking a California orange was as sweet and delicious as eating one - \u003cem\u003eand\u003c\/em\u003e held the promise of a healthy life. \u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn 176 full-color pages and more than 250 images, author David Boule shares the fastcinating story of the orange's impact on the culture - historic, financial, and yes, romantic - of California. And at the same time, he shows and tells the vivid tale of citriculture - the complex and captivating world of growing the orange and its juicy cousins. \u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHistory lovers will marvel as Boule traces the orange's origins back to Southeast Asia, and links the roots of its influence on California all the way back to Califia, a fictional warrior queen whose name became bona fide history. From its earliest days, the dream of California has been that it is a place of plenty, of potential, of personal opportunity.\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDavid Boule brings the world of the orange and California to the coffee table. Drink it all in; savor every last drop. This is \u003cem\u003eThe Orange and the Dream of California\u003c\/em\u003e.\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan style=\"line-height: 1.4;\"\u003eHardcover coffee table book\u003c\/span\u003e\u003c\/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan style=\"line-height: 1.4;\"\u003e176 pages\u003c\/span\u003e\u003c\/li\u003e\n\u003c\/ul\u003e","brand":"Angel City Press","offers":[{"title":"Default Title","offer_id":1812556675,"sku":"105429","price":35.0,"currency_code":"USD","in_stock":true}],"thumbnail_url":"\/\/cdn.shopify.com\/s\/files\/1\/0877\/4476\/products\/TheOrange.jpeg?v=1432665729","url":"http:\/\/shop.lfla.org\/products\/the-orange-the-california-dream","provider":"The Library Store","version":"1.0","type":"link"}